This paper is about a deep generative model that uses adversarial kernel learning techniques to improve the performance and computational efficiency of the original Generative Moment Matching Network (GMMN). The paper evaluates the proposed method on multiple benchmark datasets, including image datasets such as MNIST, CIFAR-10, CelebA, and LSUN. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper proposes a new distance measure and optimization method, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) are also possible sub-categories.
